<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="343" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1590,1615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[863,926,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">nigri-</emphasis>
(black) and 
<emphasis box="[1076,1146,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">fuscus</emphasis>
(brown), referring to the blackish brown forewing.
</paragraph>
